r=#FF9933 class=headings><font color=#330066>Author</font></td><td valign=top bgcolor=#FF9933 class=headings><font color=#330066>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/ugrovetreesong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grove Treesong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Primal Ooze</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/11/02 9:39:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1864.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Very disappointed in my first pet. Does it get better?</span><hr size=1> Greetings everyone. I just reached level 9 with my Troll beastlord and was happy to see the birth of  Lockjaw jr, my first pet. <br><br>I had read that the first pet is level 9. But when I con my pet (at level 9) he gives the message: &quot;looks like you would have the upper hand&quot;, i.e. the high green message. The colour of the message is also green.  Not only that, but he sucks monkeyballs in combat! He misses about 1/3 to 1/2 of the time  when he fights a level 1! creature, and when I try to take a blue with him, I might as well leave him home: he does maybe 1/10 th of the damage that I myself am doing, while I have not even maxed out my H2H skill yet. Trying a yellow or even con: haha!  I thought our pet ruled! My first Necropet would OWN this lil alligator! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Just got killed by a blue snake, and I was so pissed because the pet did NO damage at all, the snake had me for lunch. a blue snake!  I am untwinked, but defense is maxed, H2H is about 2/3, offense is maxed, and I have 172 AC, which is not so bad at level 9. Big bummer!  Please tell me this gets better?<br><br>Thanks!<br><br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/uterrixs.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Terrix S</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beast</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/11/02 9:44:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1864.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.shard.ws/images/bruize2.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Very disappointed in my first pet. Does it get better?</span><hr size=1> You do need to cast the 'Spirit of ...' buff spells on your pet.  In the case of a lvl 9, you need to cast Spirit of Sharik on your pet.  This boosts the pet level, and combat abilities.<br><br>Also using the spells you buff yourself with on the pet can help. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>~Bruize <p>http://www.shard.ws/images/bruize2.bmp <br>~Bruize <br>Tholluxe Paells</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/uealaniel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ealaniel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>mewling</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/11/02 9:45:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1864.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Very disappointed in my first pet. Does it get better?</span><hr size=1> You need to cast &quot;Spirit of Sharik&quot; on your pet.  That will boost it's level and combat abilities significantly.<br><br>There's a similar pet buff at every spell level.  Don't leave home without 'em. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/ugrovetreesong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grove Treesong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>mewling</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/11/02 9:51:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1864.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Very disappointed in my first pet. Does it get better?</span><hr size=1> Believe me, guys, I did that (fizzling and all....) Still bad.  What about the strangte con: is that normal with your level 9 pet? The &quot;even&quot; con message is different then what I am getting, and so is the colour of the message. I find it very strange.<br><br>Bulge, level 9 Troll BL <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/umandrike.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mandrike</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beast in Training</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/11/02 10:05:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1864.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Are you sure?</span><hr size=1> Your warder is lvl 9 when buffed. He should be at least dark blue,  if not white, black or yellow, for con. Something doesn't sound wright. Your warder is buffed to your level until you hit like lvl 30,  than they do not move in lvl's with you, but lag a few lvls behind you. Good luck<br><br>Mandrike <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/udaelfdawiz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DaelfDawiz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beast Lord</span><br>  Posts: 147<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/11/02 10:12:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1864.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Are you sure?</span><hr size=1> If you are getting a green conned warder, and you're level 9, you aren't casting the buff spell.  Once you target your warder and cast Spirit of Sharik, your pet will con even (white or black) at level 9, and dark blue for the next couple of levels.<br><br>Also, be sure you cast the spell in the zone you intend to hunt in.  If you cast the spell on the warder in Shar Vahl, and zone into Shadeweaver Thicket (for example) your pet buffs disappear and you have to rebuff him.<br><br>Be sure you have the spell, and you are casting it correctly.  I don't mean to sound demeaning...just ensuring you understand what's involved with our pets.  They are different than any other class out there, hence the usual confusion.<br><br>If all else fails, try sending a higher level beastlord on your server a tell...they may be able to give you some instruction while you're online.  <br><br>Hope that helps.<br><br>=)<br> <p><select size="1" name="D1">	<option>Kittyda Kittybangbang - 60 Savage Lord</option>	<option>Daelf Shapechanger - 60 Phantasmist</option>		<option>Dawiz Trackinwack - 53 Pathfinder</option>		<option>Damunk Chypmunk - 53 Disciple</option>		<option>Dadrood Heirlines - 52 Wanderer</option>		<option>Daneekro Mancer - 31 Necromancer</option>		<option>Dathief Smartypants - 26 Rogue</option>		<option>Dacle - 10 Cleric</option>	  </select><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=165947">Kittyda Kittybangbang's Profile</a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/ugrovetreesong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grove Treesong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>mewling</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/11/02 10:22:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1864.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Are you sure?</span><hr size=1> Thanks for all the replies guys. But there is definately something wrong.  I fought another blue snake, and now I looked at the log closely: my pet died after taking<br><br>13<br>8<br>14<br>1<br>and 7 damage......... that's a total of 43 hp.<br>I have to admit that this time he was not buffed. He died the moment he got poisoned (weak poison) by the snake. I will try again and look closer to his hp bar. But it went down FAST. I will also con him when I have him buffed, see what it sais then, WIll be back shortly. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/beqbeastlord.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=tatter999>Tatter999</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>mewling</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/11/02 10:27:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1864.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Are you sure?</span><hr size=1> I would say it is a misunderstanding in the buffing prodeedure and such ) . I hope you figure it out .. My BST pet has always rocked since L9 .. I am L 25 and my L 22 Pet still kills reds wiht a couple heals ..  and a little melee .. <br><br>Good luck friend on your BST if you get it figured out you will love this class .  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/ugrovetreesong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grove Treesong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>mewling</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/11/02 10:31:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1864.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Are you sure?</span><hr size=1> Ok, I had him buffed, and now he conned white, true enough. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Yay! He also could take a lot more damage, and was hitting the even con Orc Warrior  quit sufficiently. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>I guess it was a combination of buffs clearing after zoning, and the fact that the pet buff makes a HUGE (if not all) difference in the usefullness of your pet. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I just didnt realize it made such a difference! <br><br>Thanks all, people,  I will feed him an extra chicken this evening, he did fine with that orc warrior just now. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Cheers!<br><br>Bulge. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/udaelfdawiz.showPublicProfile?language