h no further &quot;lows&quot; like 35-38 or 44-48.  Makes sense.  Here's a &quot;light blue&quot; chart, showing you the lowest level mob you can kill for XP at each warder level.  The equation for an XP-giving mob is that it's 2/3 your level, rounded up, and at lower levels, +1 level.<br><br>9:6 (pet level 9)<br>15:11 (pet level 16)<br>22:16 (pet level 22)<br>30:21 (pet level 26)<br>39:27 (pet level 31)<br>49:34 (pet level 39)<br>54:37 (pet level 41)<br>56:38 (pet level 43)<br>58:39 (pet level 45)<br>60:40 (pet level 47)<br><br>So compare the warder levels, and if you find the right spots, it's possible from 49 on to always kill things that are blue to your pet and still get XP from them.  Looking at the chart also kind of shows why many Beastlords feel like &quot;gods&quot; from 15 through 24 or so -- their XP-giving mobs are generally even con or lower to their pets.<br><br>Of course, the reality is you'll always fight things that are red to your pet, and you'll end up tanking for her <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Good luck in the future on your Beastlord!<br><br>How'd I end up so off-topic? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/uyxmark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>yxmark</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beast Prince</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#871F78>(6/11/02 2:54:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1864.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Very disappointed in my first pet. Does it get better?</span><hr size=1> this post is LOL LOL LOL  <p>Im Sooo l33t</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><